<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-44-0484 </DOCNO><TEXT>A laser photoelectric scanning method has been employed to investigatethe influence of structural disturbed regions induced by mechanical actionsduring the treatment of Cd/sub x/Hg/sub 1-x/Te crystals and at uncontrolledlocal mechanical action (scratches, pricks etc) on their photosensitivity.A new approach has been proposed for a quantitative interpretation ofthe photosensitivity changes in the disturbed region depends on theirsize.</TEXT></DOC>